<exercise checkit-seed="0007" checkit-slug="L2" checkit-title="Truth Tables">
    <statement>
        <p>
        Construct a truth table for the following formula. Make sure your table is in the standard order and that you have included all the necessary intermediate columns.
        </p>
        <me>(\sim q \vee r) \vee \sim (\sim p \wedge r)</me>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
        The first and final columns of the truth table are
        </p>
        <m>
        \begin{array}{lllcc} \text{p} &amp; \text{q} &amp; \text{r} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{Final Column} \\ \hline \text{T} &amp; \text{T} &amp; \text{T} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{T} \\ \text{T} &amp; \text{T} &amp; \text{F} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{T} \\ \text{T} &amp; \text{F} &amp; \text{T} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{T} \\ \text{T} &amp; \text{F} &amp; \text{F} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{T} \\ \text{F} &amp; \text{T} &amp; \text{T} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{T} \\ \text{F} &amp; \text{T} &amp; \text{F} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{T} \\ \text{F} &amp; \text{F} &amp; \text{T} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{T} \\ \text{F} &amp; \text{F} &amp; \text{F} &amp; \cdots &amp; \text{T} \\ \end{array}
        </m>
    </answer>
</exercise>
